definition.value: A plastic container designed for use with parenteral drug products.
Any number of entities (members) considered as a unit.
An active process; excludes processes and mechanisms which fulfill biological functions.
A physical structure or device capable of holding objects or samples.
A person (one of unisexual specimens) who is born with genitalia and/or secondary sexual characteristics of indeterminate sex, or which combine features of both sexes.
A mix of specimens from multiple individuals representing multiple sex groups.
An individual who reports belonging to the cultural gender role distinction of male.
An individual who reports belonging to the cultural gender role distinction of female.
A way of doing something; how a result is obtained or an end is achieved.
The tangible substance that goes into the makeup of a physical object.
Knowledge derived from study, experience, or instruction that has been gathered or received by communication.
An established procedure to be followed in carrying out a given operation or in a given situation.
The basic quantity or increment used to describe the strength of a product or amount of product in a package.
The traditional unit of mass. The avoirdupois ounce is equal to 1/16 pound, or 28.349 5 grams, or 0.911 457 troy ounce.
The traditional unit of mass. By international agreement, one avoirdupois pound is equal to exactly 0.453 592 37 kilogram, 16 ounces, or 1.215 28 troy pounds.

A specific reason explaining why a meaningful value is not available. A meaningful value answers the question posed by a Data Element Concept. In contrast, a Missing Value Reason answers the implicit question "Why is there no 'meaningful' value?", when there is none.
The usual or expected function of something; the part something plays in an action or event.

label.value: Surgical Procedure by Site or System

definition.value: A categorization of surgical procedures based on surgical techniques.
A laboratory procedure to detect microorganisms in a sample.
An action or administration of therapeutic agents to produce an effect that is intended to alter or stop a pathologic process.
A laboratory test designed for the quantification of an organic or inorganic chemical within a biological specimen.
One of the possible results of an adverse event outcome that indicates that the event has improved or recuperated.

The period of time during which the embryo or fetus is present in the uterus of the female. Also describes the location of the embryo or fetus as being in the uterus in contrast to outside the uterus (ex utero).
An age group comprised of infants less than 37 weeks, 0 days gestational age.
An age group comprised of individuals between 28 days to 23 months of age.
An age group comprised of individuals between 2 to 11 years of age.
An age group comprised of individuals from 18 years to 65 years of age.
A physical object that is a device or a component or accessory of a device.
A device consisting of a narrow loop of material moving over shafts or pulleys.
An unexpected natural death from a cardiac cause within a short time period from the onset of symptoms.

A prenatal diagnostic procedure in which a small sample of amniotic fluid is removed from the uterus by a needle inserted into the abdomen. This procedure is used to detect various genetic abnormalities in the fetus and/or the sex of the fetus.
A person who gets something.
A person qualified to be engaged in activity directed at preservation of mental and physical health by diseases prevention and treatment as a source of livelihood.
A specific individual microbe and its genetically identical progeny separated on a single occasion from a sample taken from a host or culture system.
Any disorder other than abnormal tissue growth resulting from uncontrolled cell proliferation.

label.value: Non-Neoplastic Liver and Intrahepatic Bile Duct Disorder

definition.value: A non-neoplastic disorder that affects the liver parenchyma and the intrahepatic bile ducts. Representative examples include hepatitis, cirrhosis, and cholangitis.
A female individual who has had her ovaries removed.
The cessation of life due to heart abnormalities or disease.
An expected natural death from a cardiac cause. This condition usually occurs in persons with pre-existing cardiac abnormalities or disease.
The numeric, three-digit country codes specified by the ISO 3166-1 country code standard.
The two-letter country codes specified by the ISO 3166-1 country code standard.
The three-letter country codes specified by the ISO 3166-1 country code standard.
Any synthetic or animal-derived agent that is chemically identical or similar to an endogenous hormone with therapeutic application.
Information regarding the means of contacting a person or group.
